                                <h1>Avast Internet Security</h1>
                                <h2>Set an Exception for your IP Camera</h2>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    In some cases it can be that the virus scanner "Avast" is blocking the video stream of the camera. Actually it blocks the ActiveX and Quicktime Plugin from receiving the cameras video stream. In this case you will need to set an exception in Avast so it does not block the camera anymore.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 1</strong>: Please open the program Avast by clicking the Avast symbol on the right side of the windows task bar. Another way is to open the start menue and to choose the program directly. Once opened please click Settings on the upper right side.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
